= Tab Blocks

Tab blocks allow you to organize content into tabs for better presentation.

== Basic Tabs

_|_#tab1[name="First Tab"]
Content for the first tab.

_|_#tab2[name="Second Tab"]
Content for the second tab.

_|_#tab3[name="Third Tab"]
Content for the third tab.

_|_

== Tabs with Multiple Paragraphs

_|_#mac[name="macOS"]
This is content for macOS.

It can contain multiple paragraphs.

And even lists:

* Item one
* Item two

_|_#windows[name="Windows"]
This is content for Windows.

Windows content can also have multiple paragraphs.

_|_#linux[name="Linux"]
This is content for Linux.

Linux content here.

_|_

== Tabs with Code Blocks

_|_#javascript[name="JavaScript"]
[source,javascript]
----
console.log("Hello from JavaScript");
----

_|_#python[name="Python"]
[source,python]
----
print("Hello from Python")
----

_|_#ruby[name="Ruby"]
[source,ruby]
----
puts "Hello from Ruby"
----

_|_

== Tabs with Mixed Content

_|_#example1[name="Example 1"]
This tab has *bold* and _italic_ text.

And a code block:

[source]
----
example code
----

_|_#example2[name="Example 2"]
This tab has different content.

With a list:

* First item
* Second item

_|_

